# Git commits

- Write commit messages as normal project commits only.
- Do NOT add Cursor, AI, agent, or co-author attribution.
- Do NOT include lines such as `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or `Made-with: Cursor`.
- Do NOT pass `--trailer` on any git commit command.
- Use concise conventional subjects (e.g. `fix(recruiter):`, `feat(nurse):`).
- Body text should describe user-visible or operational changes only.

## How to commit from the agent (Windows)

Cursor's terminal may rewrite `git commit` and inject co-author trailers. Always use one of:

1. `C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe commit -F .git/COMMIT_MSG_CLEAN.tmp` (write message to the file first), or
2. `.\scripts\git-commit-clean.ps1 -Subject "fix: summary" -Body "optional details"`

Never use bare `git commit` in agent shell commands.

## User setup (one time)

- Cursor Settings → Agents → Attribution → turn **off** Commit Attribution and PR Attribution, then restart Cursor.
- Run `.\scripts\install-git-hooks.ps1` so `prepare-commit-msg` strips any Cursor lines that slip through.
